article.description: — Chris Harris and Eric Reed Jr. scored 19 points apiece as Southeast Missouri edged past Lipscomb 82-77 on Monday night.
article.headline: Harris, Reed lift SE Missouri over Lipscomb 82-77
article.linkText: Harris, Reed lift SE Missouri over Lipscomb 82-77
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- — Chris Harris and Eric Reed Jr. scored 19 points apiece as Southeast Missouri edged past Lipscomb 82-77 on Monday night. Nolan Taylor added 16 points and DQ Nicholas had 12 for Southeast Missouri (2-1). Jake Wolfe scored a career-high 22 points for the Bisons (1-4), whose losing streak stretched to four games. Greg Jones added 19 points and Ahsan Asadullah had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
